    • Method Detail

      • from

        @NonNull
public static @NonNull SearchFilter from(String filterString)
        Create a new SearchFilter from the provided string representation.

        The filterString argument must be a valid string search filter representation as described in RFC 4515 Section 3 - "String Search Filter Definition". This includes escaping reserved characters, such as backslash, left parenthesis, etc. This method throws an IllegalArgumentException if the filterString does not meet these requirements.

        Parameters:
        filterString - A string representation of the search filter
        Returns:
        A SearchFilter representation of the filterString.

      • getType

        @NonNull
public @NonNull SearchFilter.Type getType()
        Get the type of this search filter.

        For nested filters, the outermost type is returned. For example, this method returns SearchFilter.Type.AND for the filter (&(|(sn=Washington)(title=President)).

        Returns:
        The SearchFilter.Type enum representing the filter operation

      • getComponents

        public List<SearchFilter> getComponents()
        Get the individual filters (if any exist) that make up the current search filter.

        AND, OR, and NOT filters can be decomposed into other filters. This method returns the list of filters that compose the current filter. If the current filter cannot be further decomposed, then an empty list is returned.

        The list below shows examples of how different filters are decomposed by this method: 

         FILTER:     (title=President)
 COMPONENTS: []
 SIZE:       0

 FILTER:     (|(givenName=George)(sn=Washington)))
 COMPONENTS: [(givenName=George), (sn=Washington)]
 SIZE:       2

 FILTER:     (&(givenName=George)(sn=Washington)(title=President))
 COMPONENTS: [(givenName=George), (sn=Washington), (title=President)]
 SIZE:       3

 FILTER:     (!(title=President))
 COMPONENTS: [(title=President)]
 SIZE:       1

 FILTER:     (&(givenName=George)(|(sn=Bush)(Washington)))
 COMPONENTS: [(givenName=George), (|(sn=Bush)(Washington))]
 SIZE:       2

 FILTER:     (!(&(givenName=George)(|(sn=Bush)(Washington))))
 COMPONENTS: [(&(givenName=George)(|(sn=Bush)(Washington)))]
 SIZE:       1
        Returns:
        the list of individual components if this is an AND, OR, or NOT filter. Otherwise, an empty list.

      • getAssertionValue

        @NonNull
public @NonNull Optional<String> getAssertionValue()
        Get the assertion value of this filter, represented as a string.

        This method is applicable to filter types:

        • SearchFilter.Type.PRESENCE
        • SearchFilter.Type.EQUAL
        • SearchFilter.Type.GREATER_OR_EQUAL
        • SearchFilter.Type.LESS_OR_EQUAL
        • SearchFilter.Type.SUBSTRING
        • SearchFilter.Type.APPROXIMATE_MATCH
        • SearchFilter.Type.EXTENSIBLE_MATCH
        All other filter types return an empty Optional.
        Returns:
        An Optional containing the assertion value if one exists.
